# Skills Section Guide

This document provides specific guidance for working with the Skills section in the portfolio.

## Skills Section Structure

The Skills section in [pages/index.tsx](mdc:pages/index.tsx) is organized into a 2x2 grid of skill cards:

1. Programming
2. Cybersecurity
3. Prompt Engineering
4. Microsoft Office & Editing

Each card follows the same structure but with different content patterns.

## Skill Card Types

### 1. Grid-Based Skill Cards (Programming, Microsoft Office)

These use a grid layout of icons with labels:

```tsx
<div className="tech-skills-container">
  <div className="tech-skills-grid">
    <div className="tech-skill-item">
      <div className="tech-skill-icon">
        <IconComponent />
      </div>
      <div className="tech-skill-name">Skill Name</div>
    </div>
    {/* More skill items */}
  </div>
</div>
```

### 2. Badge-Based Skill Cards (Cybersecurity)

These use badge lists and detailed descriptions:

```tsx
<div className="d-flex flex-wrap mb-3">
  {['Skill 1', 'Skill 2', 'Skill 3'].map((skill) => (
    <span key={skill} className="skill-badge">
      {skill}
    </span>
  ))}
</div>

<div className="cybersec-skills-container">
  <Row className="g-3">
    <Col md={6}>
      <div className="cybersec-skill-item">
        <div className="d-flex align-items-center">
          <div className="cybersec-skill-icon me-3">
            <IconComponent />
          </div>
          <div>
            <h5 className="h6 mb-1">Skill Name</h5>
            <p className="small mb-0">Skill description</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </Col>
    {/* More skill items */}
  </Row>
</div>
```

### 3. Row-Based Skill Cards (Prompt Engineering)

These use row layout with icons and detailed descriptions:

```tsx
<div className="prompt-skills-container flex-grow-1">
  <Row className="g-3">
    <Col md={6}>
      <div className="prompt-skill-item">
        <div className="d-flex align-items-center">
          <div className="prompt-skill-icon me-3">
            <IconComponent />
          </div>
          <div>
            <h5 className="h6 mb-1">Skill Name</h5>
            <p className="small mb-0">Skill description</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </Col>
    {/* More skill items */}
  </Row>
</div>
```

## Icon Usage Guidelines

- For technical skills: Use `react-icons/fa` for most icons
- For software/platforms: Use `react-icons/si` for branded icons
- Custom SVG: Use inline SVG for specialized icons

## Adding/Modifying Skills

When adding or modifying skills:

1. Use the appropriate skill card structure based on the category
2. Maintain consistent styling and layout patterns
3. Use appropriate icons from the existing icon libraries
4. Follow the established content format for descriptions


